data.title: James Kaufman Weds Amy Bach
data.text:
Amy Elizabeth Bach, a daughter of Linda J. Bach and Richard J. Bach, both of New Rochelle, N.Y., and James Lobach Kaufman, a son of Dr. and Mrs. Richard J. Kaufman of New Rochelle and New York, were married yesterday at the Old Dutch Church of Sleepy Hollow in North Tarrytown, N.Y. The Rev. David Smith, an Episcopal priest, performed the ceremony.

Mrs. Kaufman, 31 years old, graduated from the Parsons School of Design. She owns a jewelry-design concern in New Rochelle. Her father owns the Mechanics Tool Service, a machinery and tool sales company there. Her mother is the president of Linda Bach Enterprises, a garment-design company in New York.

Mr. Kaufman, 33, graduated from the University of Miami, where he also received a master's degree in psychology, and he holds a master's degree in social work from Columbia University. He is a psychotherapist for Westchester Jewish Community Services in White Plains.

His mother, known professionally as Dr. Katherine S. Lobach, is the assistant New York City commissioner for child and adolescent health services. His father is an attending oncologist at the Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center in New York. The bridegroom's first marriage ended in divorce.
